I’m and FRC alumni from team 319 currently getting my masters in Denmark at SDU. For my thesis I’m designing a mobile robot to clean up parks and sidewalks. I’m finding its a little more difficult over here to source parts and was wondering if anyone had advice on places to get parts or if any FRC teams have old components like the old power distribution boards collecting dust they’d be willing to sell?
Thanks in advance!

REV has a warehouse in the EU, which could be useful: https://revrobotics.eu

For things like power distribution though, I’d look at the automotive aftermarket and source from an auto parts store local to you. Distributing 12-24VDC in a way that’s resilient to heat and vibration is a solved problem, PDB/PDP/PDHs just added some (significant!) quality of life features for teams.

Billfred:

Distributing 12-24VDC in a way that’s resilient to heat and vibration is a solved problem, PDB/PDP/PDHs just added some (significant!) quality of life features for teams.

The CTRE power distribution panel is nice, but at its most basic form (the raw PCB) is available for purchase in the US via CTREs website. You then add fuses to each line, add niceties of screw terminals for your battery cord attachment, maybe some kind of reusable wire clip attached to the fuses and PCB and voila. That’s all a Power Distribution Panel is, plus some can signaling (probably not needed in this case)
